<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 5:48PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Meriwether and northeastern Troup Counties through 615 PM EDT...
At 548 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Louise, or 9 miles
northeast of LaGrange, moving southwest at 10 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
LaGrange, Hogansville, Lone Oak, Saint Marks, Louise and Mountville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
